	<FactionDef ParentName="FactionBase">
		<defName>DRG_Civil</defName>
		<label>Outcast refugees</label>
		<description>War refugees from a fallen industrial world. When their homeworld was overrun by the mechanoids and the Empire's reinforcements never came, the survivors scattered across the rimworlds in search of stability they no longer had.\n\nThey carry Imperial weapons, composite armor, and the discipline of subjects who once belonged to something larger. With their homeworld gone, they cannot replace what breaks or replenish what runs out. They retain spacer technology by inheritance, not by capacity. Their settlements are provisional by necessity and permanent by hope: charters and compacts drawn up around campfires, founding documents signed by people who remember being citizens.\n\nResilient, charitable, and fiercely cooperative, they make excellent allies and stubborn enemies.</description>
		<pawnSingular>outcast</pawnSingular>
		<pawnsPlural>outcasts</pawnsPlural>
		<listOrderPriority>13</listOrderPriority>
		<settlementGenerationWeight>1</settlementGenerationWeight>
		<requiredCountAtGameStart>1</requiredCountAtGameStart>
		<maxCountAtGameStart>1</maxCountAtGameStart>
